GH Consults LLC (“GHC”) is a corporate advisory firm specializing in Vietnamese economic policies and laws. With a strong track record spanning several years, GHC has solidified its distinctive position in providing expert assistance to multinational clients across various project works. Our areas of expertise include anti-dumping, anti-subsidy, international trade disputes, M&A, investments, advertising, promotion, and other compliance support activities. Throughout our engagement with clients, we have cultivated trusted co-operative relationships and collaborated closely with top-tier Vietnamese and international law firms.

GHC is currently in search of an Senior Analyst (Accounting & Finance) to join its dynamic team and play a pivotal role in the execution and management of advisory projects. An Senior Analyst (Accounting & Finance) at GHC shall take an active role in examining financial and accounting records to conduct in-depth analysis and formulate legal advice and/or arguments thereof.

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES

At GHC, an Analyst (Accounting & Finance) will:
> Interact with the Client to collect financial and accounting data needed for execution of project;
> Conduct research on a wide variety of regulatory, political, and economic issues in support of the project work, through open-source research and engagement with relevant stakeholders;
> Work closely with team to conduct in-depth analysis of the collected data;
> Develop legal arguments based on sound analysis of financial and accounting data;
> Build and maintain productive working relationships with clients and relevant stakeholders;
> Support the management in executing business development activities, such as developing proposals, meeting with potential clients, participating in net-working events; and
> Undertake other projects and firm development works as assigned.

